  section.definition
    h3 Definition
    p.main-definition A Hire Quote is an offer made to a customer for the rental of vehicle models and included add-ons for a specified period. The customer may be an individual or a company. The quote is prepared and sent by Service Manager when the manager decides to do so. An email is generated and sent to the customer's nominated email address. It includes references to supporting documents and photos.
    dl.dl-horizontal
      dt Uid
      dd A system-generated number for the Hire Quote. 
      dt Version Number
      dd An amendment to a hire quote results in an increase of the version number. All the details in the previous version are preserved for future reference.
      dt Reference
      dd The reference combines the uid and version number to form a unique reference number for the Hire Quote in the format HQ-AAnnnn-1. The number at the end is the version number.
      dt Customer
      dd The client to whom the quote is presented.
      dt Enquiry Reference
      dd If the hire quote was created in response to an enquiry, a cross-reference to that enquiry will be available.

